From a regulatory / governance point of view, it is a more sustainable change if you move an issue out of a project into another project, than changing an issue type within a project using the move function.

Although Jira quick search forwards the the [Old_Project_Key]-[Old_Number] to the corresponding new issue key, the original issue key will be lost (i.e. won't show up in any filters), which complicates traceability. 

Therefore we suggest that the right to move an issue from one project to another can be controlled separately from the right to move an issue _within_ a project, so that we can apply more restrictions to the group of people who are allowed to do the former operation.

