We are using ServiceRocket's SF & JIRA Cloud connector that links SF cases to JIRA issues (objects). Since the JIRA value limit for the custom field value holds maximum of 255 characters, the unique IDs generated from the linkage sums up to about 13 linkages max total. However, there are instances where there are more than 13 SF cases linked/associated to 1 JIRA ticket, this creates problems. One of the problem being that the latter links replace the older ones. Also, only actively linked SF cases to that 1 JIRA ticket get automatically synched. This causes the other inactive linked SF cases to reflect the wrong status or data - causing reporting and metric inefficiencies and inaccuracies.

Here is what was suggested instructions by the Servicerocket Support rep:
"The Remote System Reference is using Salesforce Object ID and stored in JIRA database (STRINGVALUE column in CUSTOMFIELDVALUE table). The STRINGVALUE is 'VARCHAR2(255 CHAR)' so it only can store up to 13 Salesforce Object Id. "

